  "text": "Morphologically Rich Languages (SPMRL) Shared Task 2013 [CITATION_1] . 5 We follow the official split for training, development and testing set. We use the core set of 12 POS categories provided by [CITATION_2] . In the second Arabic dataset, the training set is a dependency conversion of the Arabic Treebank, which primarily in- [CITATION_3] . Table 2 summarizes the statistics of the datasets. For the SPMRL test set, we follow the common practice which limits the sentence lengths up to 70 [CITATION_4] . For classical Arabic and Chinese, we evaluate on all the test sentences.",
